White Wine Quality Analysis by Priyaranjan JC.

Data set contains white variants of the Portuguese Vinho Verde wine. Number of Instances of white wine - 4898. Number of Attributes: 11 + output attribute(quality)

Description for Atrributes and Output Variable :

  • X : serial number for instances.

  • fixed acidity: most acids involved with wine or fixed or nonvolatile (do not evaporate readily)

  • volatile acidity: the amount of acetic acid in wine, which at too high of levels can lead to an unpleasant, vinegar taste

  • citric acid: found in small quantities, citric acid can add freshness and flavor to wines

  • residual sugar: the amount of sugar remaining after fermentation stops, its rare to find wines with less than 1 gram/liter and wines with greater than 45 grams/liter are considered sweet.

  • chlorides: the amount of salt in the wine

  • free sulfur dioxide: the free form of SO2 exists in equilibrium between molecular SO2 (as a dissolved gas) and bisulfite ion; it prevents microbial growth and the oxidation of wine

  • total sulfur dioxide: amount of free and bound forms of S02; in low concentrations, SO2 is mostly undetectable in wine, but at free SO2 concentrations over 50 ppm, SO2 becomes evident in the nose and taste of wine

  • density: the density of water is close to that of water depending on the percent alcohol and sugar content

  • pH: describes how acidic or basic a wine is on a scale from 0 (very acidic) to 14 (very basic); most wines are between 3-4 on the pH scale

  • sulphates: a wine additive which can contribute to sulfur dioxide gas (S02) levels, which acts as an antimicrobial and antioxidant

  • alcohol: the percent alcohol content of the wine

  • quality : Contains a score between 0 and 10.

Wine Quality

Quality variable is unbalanced.It follows a normal distribution.Wine having quality 6 is the most common wine.

Fixed.Acidity

fixed acidity ranges between 3.8 and 14.2. But most of the values are distributed acrsoo 5.5 to 8.5 range. Considering only 0.95 quantile data(removing outliers) for visualization.

Fixed acidity property of the wine follows mostly a normal distribution between 5th and 95th percentile of the values.

Volatile Acidity

High amounts of volatile.acidity will make the wine taste like vinegar.So,most of the acidity is below 0.48 percent.

After removing outliers(95th percent quantile),we can observe that volatile.acidity follows a near normal distribution. In futher investigation we need to find if acidity above 0.48 will result in low quality wines.

Citric Acid

Citric acid is in very low quantitles when compared to fixed acid percent.It is more in the range of volatile acid range.There are few wines with nearly zero citirc acid percent. Range of citric acid is between 0.00 and 1.66.But most the values reside between 0.2 and 0.5.

Between 5th and 95th percentile, citric acid moslty follows normal distribution.

Residual sugar

Most of the values in Resudual sugar are between 0-20.But there are few very large values. In log x axis scale, residual sugar follows a bimodal distribution.

Lot of the wines has residual sugar values of around 1.5 and residual values are uniformly distributed from 3 to 16.

chlorides

Chlorides between 5th and 95th percentile has normal distribution.

Free sulphur dioxide

Most of free sulfur dioxide content is between rangte 0 and 80. There are few very high values of free.sulfur.dioxide.

Between 5th and 95th percentile of free.sulfur.dioxide values follow a normal distribution. #### Total sulfur dioxide

Density

After Removing the outliers,Density distribution is little closer to normal distribution.

ph

Between 5th and 95th percentile ,pH values follow a normal distribution.

sulphates

sulphate values lies between 0.2 and 1 values. Most of the suphate values are present between 0.35 to 0.65. between 5th and 95th percentile ,sulphate values follow a normal distribution.

Alcohol

Range of the alcohol is between 8.5 and 14.

Most of the values of the alcohol are present between 8.75 and 12.75.

total acidity

total acidity percent of wine is between 5.5 and 8.5.

Between 5th and 95th percentile values total acidity follows normal distribution.

Univariate Analysis

What is the structure of your dataset?

There are total of 4898 white wine samples. There are 10 properties of the white wine which define the quality of the wine.

Quality of the samples form a normal distribution with quality 6 as the most common quality. alcohol,density and chlorides are the most correlated with the quality. Most of the wines has the alcohol content of 9.5 and alcohol percent continues to increase till 14% with decreasing count of samples. Most of the wine has density between 0.9871 and 1.Few wines are above density 1. chlorides are distributed between in the range of 0.009 and 0.309.But majority of wines are in the range of 0.029 and 0.054.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?

Almost all of the varialbes(except residual sugar) have a similar distribution.Values between 5th and 95th values follows a normal like distribution.All of the varialbes has values beyond 2 standard deviation from mean. Residual sugar forms a bimodal distribution when scaled by log across x-axis.

What other features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?

Volatile acidity, total sulphur dioxide,residual sugar are directly related to taste of the wine. Improper proportions of these will lead to bad taste of wine.

Did you create any new variables from existing variables in the dataset?

Total acidity in the wine is created by combining fixed acidity and volatile acidity. Quality variable is changed from numeric format to factor type.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?

All of the varialbes has few values beyond 3 standard deviatations from the mean.When observed between 5th and 95th values, most of these varialbes followed normal distribution.Does the values beyond 3 standard deviation,directly result in very poor or very good wine quality?,this has to futher investigated.
